1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,440
Etiology defines prognosis.

2
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:04,800
Giant cell myocarditis carries the worst outcomes

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,160
— up to 62.5 percent death or

4
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:11,520
transplant within 60 days — driven by

5
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:14,880
aggressive macrophage and multinucleated giant cell infiltration.

6
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:18,240
Eosinophilic myocarditis, often hypersensitivity-mediated, shows 26.3 percent

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,600
cardiac death or transplant at 60 days.

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,960
Lymphocytic myocarditis — the most common subtype

9
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:28,320
— reports 21 percent at 60 days

10
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:31,200
but a more variable long-term course.
